comments.body:
@mtrmac @runcom We have decided to use localhost/ to represent locally created images. We know this potentially conflicts with users setting up a registry at localhost, But the user has an easy work around if this causes an issue.  IE I can not tell the difference between locally created images and images I pulled from localhost, by setting up the registry with a different name like localhost.com or something and adding an entry to the /etc/hosts file.

This is much better then what we have now in that we can't tell the difference between images created at locally and those pulled from docker.io.  It also eliminates the need for a breaking change to containers/image.

@baude @mheon These changes will also need to be made to podman once we have it working in buildah.  

Note: Nalin has also found lots of issues where we were not looking through the registries for certain image interactions.
